explanation: This solution uses dynamic programming to build a 2D array dp, where dp[i][j] represents the length of the longest common subsequence of the first i characters of text1 and the first j characters of text2. The solution iterates through the characters of both strings, and for each pair of characters, it checks if they are the same. If they are, it increments the length of the common subsequence by 1; otherwise, it takes the maximum length of the common subsequences of the previous characters. The solution returns the length of the longest common subsequence of the entire strings.

